@node "REGISTER" "How to register"
@next "KEYFILE"
@prev "COPYRIGHTS"

  @{u}A registration is possible in two ways:@{uu}

  1) @{u}via snail mail@{uu}

     - You can pay by remittance or with a cheque.
     - The @{"keyfile" link "KEYFILE" 0} will be send on a disk (HD or DD).
       Please send me an Amiga-formated disk and a prepaid enveloped with your
       address. You will then get the latest version of TUMID.
     - The @{"registration form" system "ed TUMID.regist"} can be placed on the disk as ASCII-file or added
       separatly as a print-out.

  2) @{u}via eMail@{uu}

     - You can pay by remittance or with a cheque.
     - The @{"keyfile" link "KEYFILE" 0} will be send via eMail. Obviously you have to enter your
       eMail address in the @{"registration form" system "ed TUMID.regist"}.
       The current T.U.M.ID. version will not be send by eMail, however you can
       always find it in Aminet or on my homepage.
     - Please send the @{"registration form" system "ed TUMID.regist"} as ASCII-file to my
       @{"eMail address" link "AUTOR" 0}.

  Registrations and @{"keyfile" link "KEYFILE" 0}-distribution via eMail are handled with priority,
  however I will try to handle snail mail registrations as fast as possible, too.

  See also the @{"copyright terms" link "COPYRIGHTS" 0} and the @{"registration form" system "ed TUMID.regist"}!

@endnode

@node "KEYFILE" "Keyfiles` function"
@next "AUTOR"
@prev "REGISTER"

  @{b}As a registered user you will get a keyfile that contains your name
  and a specific personal code.@{ub}

  If this file is not found or defective you may only test the program but
  not use it regularily. A small requester will pop up from time to time
  to remember you of the missing registration.

  @{u}Notice@{uu}: The keyfile is for your personal use only! Do not give it to
  someone else!

  @{b}Place the keyfile into the programs' directory.@{ub}
  On the next start the program will find the keyfile and check it automatically.

  See also the @{"copyright terms" link "COPYRIGHTS" 0}!

@endnode

